Meet <b>Dellz</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Dellz lives at <a href='/home/?user=dellz'>52131 Castle Hill</a> in one of the roomy houses of Westridge.  He's only been a resident since January 11, 2005, but his fellow citizens are already quite fond of him!<br><br>Despite the excitement of moving to a new place, Dellz has been quite calm about the transition.  In fact, his friends say he is always calm and collected, and that his composure has helped them out of tight situations more than once!  <br><br>Besides always keeping a cool head, Dellz is also quite smart.  He's solved many of his friends' problems with clever solutions.  He's also solved a few math problems of his own, as his golden trophy for Countdown! indicates.  Math is one of his favorite subjects, as Dellz's teachers at Millsberry Academy will be quick to tell you.  His other favorite topic is chemistry; his interest and bright mind have made him a regular at the lab.<br><br>Outside of school, Dellz likes to devote his time to mysteries.  He will be the first to tell you that there's nothing more exciting than a good, suspenseful mystery.  He has a huge collection of mystery novels, stacked right next to his stockpile of reggae, rap, and disco CDs.  Dellz's appreciation of music has helped him become a quick study at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/studio/">Millsberry Recording Studio</a>, where he's already mixed a couple of <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/home/?user=dellz">tracks</a>.<br><br>With the nice summer weather coming in, however, you'll most likely find Dellz outdoors!  If he's not at his best friend's house hanging out, Dellz is usually in his backyard, solving his own mysteries.  Once in a while, he and his friends enjoy taking a fun trip to an amusement park.  If you happen to be outside too, look for his white, green, or red t-shirts if you want to say hi!<br><br>Thanks for being a fine citizen, Dellz, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!